ASSISTANT SCIENTIST - CIENTISTA JUNIOR
Descrição
General Description
Execute R&D activities for the implementation of projects related to products,
materials and technologies for Engineered Products for existing business and
support troubleshooting related to manufacturing/production areas.
Responsabilities
Support the implementation of the new specifications for SMP projects and
guarantee adherence;
Support, plan and execute production trials for SMP projects;
Sense of urgency is needed to proactively respond to problems and
opportunities;
Proactively investigates and develops improvements to existing processes or
develops new and improved processes;
Participate in cross-functional project teams;
Provide critical business information to organizational leaders;
Ability to manage complexity and to work collaboratively with business
partners;
Execute laboratory analysis, compile and analyze data, identify causes, draw
conclusions and generate reports;
Qualificações
A minimum of Bachelor degree in Material Engineering, Chemical Engineering,
Biochemistry Engineering, Chemistry, or related areas is required;
Experience in Product Development of Consumer Products is a differential;
Knowledge in the field of adhesive, nonwovens or fibers is desirable;
Advanced English is required;
Good communication skills within different areas & team work.

